text: Acleris rubivorella is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in southern European RussiaFauna Europaea and Kazakhstan. The larvae feed on Betula, Malus, Spiraea, Polygonum and Rubus species.Acleris at funet ==References== Category:Moths described in 1962 rubivorella Category:Moths of Russia Category:Moths of Asia
